I"¡<p>The United States is swimming in natural gas, and China has a huge appetite for the relatively clean and efficient fuel to power its economy as it shifts away from coal. That dynamic was on display from 2016 to 2017, when Chinese purchases of liquefied natural gas (LNG) from the United States increased by nearly six-fold, resulting in China buying nearly 15 percent of all U.S. LNG exports.</p>

